Saturday December 3rd - 12-4 p.m. 
Barnes & Noble Tuscaloosa (Midtown Village)
USA TODAY Bestselling Author LYNESSA LAYNE will be meeting readers, chatting and signing her international bestselling  mystery thriller suspense romance novels, so drop by while you're Christmas shopping and pick up a personalized gift for your favorite readers...and treat  yourself, too! 🎄🎁🎅

* Lynessa is a 2022 (x2) Mystery Writers of America Silver Falchion Award Finalist (Best Suspense & Readers'Choice).
* She's been featured in Mystery & Suspense Magazine, cover story of GEMS Magazine, Knoxville Voyager Magazine, news and television, is a winner of the Writer's Digest 2017 Short Story Contest (out of over 5,200 entrants), and has recently completed her 2022 book signing tour spanning Arizona to Florida to Pennsylvania to the Dakotas and a dozen other states across the country.
* For more info., check out www.LynessaLayne.com and connect on social media (FB, Twitter, Instagram, BookBub, Goodreads and AllAuthor).

* This is a multi-author, multi-genre book signing event featuring several Bestselling, award winning members of the Tuscaloosa Writers & Illustrators Guild.

Pugsy is not impressed. 🤣

Started working on a special project yesterday with hubs. I have a feeling it's going to blow your minds - something no one else has ever done (to my knowledge). Stay tuned for more.
Also, hub's YA paranormal series book one is at 12k of a projected 50k, it's CLEAN (13-113 - no cursing or romance beyond puppy love) and it's GOOD. He's writing it for our 14 y.o., wants to have it in paperback in time for her 15th birthday in January - she's beyond excited - said it's all she wants for her bday 🥰 I'll be co-authoring / developmental editing & publishing the series with him - family project including the kids after the first one - input from our four girls to guide the (mis) adventures of the 16 y.o. main character and her band of neighborhood friends. 🤓👍 Lots of humor, ookie spooky investigations and teen angst for the Scooby Doo lovers who've grown out of cartoons but still crave a good mystery with some real and teen-imagined paranormal themes. 💕
Skittles taking a bottle 🍼 while some of our chickens peck for crumble on the front porch 💕

It's a cold, rainy day here, but Pugsy has the right idea.😴💤👍 Perfect nap weather. 

Side note - I'm at over 160,000 words on DCYE #7 and on a three-day roll 🧑‍💻 - might have to break this one up into two books! 😯

Faith, Hope and Love from our home to yours. Praying the new year brings blessings immeasurable to all of us and healing to all who need it. ❤️

As we ring in the New Year, I want to thank everyone who made 2022 THE best year of our lives. Family, friends, readers, authors, event organizers, vendors, models, venue staff and the people we met along the way. 💕
This year, we:
😲 Traveled over 20,000 miles (all by car).
😲 Adventured through: Arizona, New Mexico, Nevada, Utah, Wyoming, North Dakota, South Dakota, Nebraska, Kansas, Missouri, Arkansas, Texas, Mississippi, Louisiana, Alabama, Florida, Georgia, South Carolina, North Carolina, Tennessee, Kentucky, Indiana, Ohio, Pennsylvania and West Virginia... HALF (25) of the United States!
😲 Met THOUSANDS of readers, authors, models and vendors at 16 book signing events and in-between!
😲 Went to Mystery Writers of America's Killer Nashville Awards Dinner 🍽️ as an invited Finalist! 💃
😲 Received an invitation to the Edgar Awards in NYC from Mystery Writers of America! (Was unable to attend, unfortunately.)
🥰 Made so many new friends and acquaintances!
🏆Made the USA TODAY Bestseller List with a stellar team of authors, and phenomenal organizer, Ashley Zakrzewski.
🤓 Learned so much from and about everyone we met.
🤣 Shared a LOT of laughter!
😢 Shared some tears, too.
😢 Lost friends, family, and our beloved and faithful 12-year-old bull mastiff, Phoebe (we held her as she passed). Tomorrow isn't guaranteed...love deeply and care selflessly like there is no tomorrow. Forgive, even if you can't forget. Let those you love, adore and appreciate know how you feel about them often. Pay kindness forward every chance you get. It's more rewarding and fulfilling than a boatload of money or things, and it brightens people's days even in the worst of times.
🤔 All things considered, no year is perfect, but this was a pretty darn good one, and we thank you for being in it. 💕
God bless you all, and we look forward to sharing 2023 with you. 🥰
HAPPY NEW YEAR !!! 🎉
New Year's Eve with my Bama bestie Serenity, and our families 💕🥳🎉🥂🍾

Happy New Year ❣️🎉

Two years ago I had my second 'Books&Bands solo book signing at the legendary Carl's Country on highway 4 outside the city limits. After nearly 50 years, Carl's is no more. From Willy Nelson to Hank III and Brandon Jordan, it's seen just about every up and coming country act and superstar perform or hop onstage to join in with the band. To be part of the history and sign 'the wall' was an experience I'll never forget. The bar has, at last, changed hands, is renamed, and is under renovation. It'll be interesting to see the place when the new owner opens the doors. He promises the same great, cozy live music atmosphere with a new look... There's just something about a place that's seen so much music history. Hoping the place doesn't lose its charm. 🎸❤️‍🔥🙏

At the family ranch in Texas last Thanksgiving.. Definitely our happy place. Please pray for hub's parents. So many happy years visiting them, but Pop is dying of bone cancer (agent orange from his time in Vietnam), and Mom is in late stage Alzheimer's with dementia. Don't know how to cope and adjust to going back there without them. 😭

How do we say goodbye? Hubs and I are at a loss. His dad passed away this afternoon. We'd just talked to him on the phone today,..20 minutes later, we got word he was gone. So many memories. Such a good man. We miss you already, Pop. Praying you're enjoying your honeydew melon 🍈 in heaven tonight. 🙏😭✝️ R.I.P. Master Sergeant Giles, USMC ret.

Locked Up In Ohio 2021 - The Ohio State Reformatory in Mansfield Ohio (where Shawshank Redemption was filmed). Definitely haunted, beyond a shadow figure of a doubt. What a place for my first big book signing event! They say you leave an imprint on some locations you visit. And some locations leave an imprint on you. This one had all the makings of both. 👻

Even in the worst of times, God sends something beautiful to remind us he loves us, that we'll get through the hard times. This beautiful peacock 🦚 (my favorite bird) has visited us and roosted above our diner seats on the back deck at the ranch, unfettered by us sitting there, and perfectly content to join us at sunset, since we returned to the ranch to take care of hub's mom when his pop passed. All the other peacocks roost on top of the barn except this one. He never roosted here before, but started calling this spot his, the day we arrived (the day after Pop passed). A ray of joy in this otherwise difficult phase of life. God telling us Pop is with him now, that everything is going to be okay, and he sent a sign to let us know he's honored his promise... John 3:16 🙏 Thank you for our daily reminder, Lord. ✝️💕

Kinsley's in the wind. For her own good. Hard to let her go, but too damn dangerous to keep her. Back to business as usual for Klive King. Even so, he can't seem to shake the effect she's had on him. Klive keeps a tail on her, but can he handle her moving on...without him? Regardless, there are deals to be made, marks to kill, and traps to be set. No rest for the wicked, right? But when other men set their sights on the one that got away, can Klive handle the consequences of his decision to cut her loose? Will Kins just end up a footnote of tainted love in his little black book of lies and alibis? Or will Klive reclaim his turf - and his woman - up close and personal? Point blank.
